Ethanol Is Capping Global Sugar Production, ISO’s Baron Says

-- B y   L u z i   A n n   J a v i e r
-- 
2011-08-15T02:03:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/ethanol-is-capping-global-sugar-production-iso-s-baron-says.html
The production of ethanol is putting
a ceiling on global output of sugar and ethanol-blend mandates
are “spreading like bushfires,” said  Peter Baron , executive
director of the  International Sugar Organization , at a
conference in the  Philippines .  "Ethanol mandates are spreading like bushfires and this is
irreversible," said Baron. Biofuel is capping sugar-output
growth in countries including Brazil, Thailand and  India , he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Luzi Ann Javier in Singapore at 
 ljavier@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
